frameDefinitions: An Entity loses moisture with the outcome of being in a dry state.
An Agent causes a Dryee (either a surface or an entire entity, inside and out) to become dry.
An Agent affects an Artifact so that it is no longer capable of performing its inherent function.
Through use, a Resource is diminished in quality or quantity (up to complete attrition) such that it becomes less capable of sustaining future use.
A Killer or Cause causes the death of the Victim.
frameExamples: My entire life savings is <t>depleted</t> due to university and medical bills.
listRoleDefinitions: The <fen>Entity</fen> is the thing that loses moisture and becomes dry.
When the <fen>Entity</fen> becomes dry.
The location where the <fen>Entity</fen> becomes dry.
The <fen>Agent</fen> is the person performing the intentional act causing the <fen>Dryee</fen> to become dry.
The <fen>Dryee</fen> is the entity which has the water removed from it.
An animate or inanimate entity, a force, or event that produces the state of dryness. Volitionality is not a necessary characteristic of <fen>Cause</fen>s.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Agent</fen> intentionally affects the <fen>Dryee</fen>.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the <fen>Agent</fen> intentionally affects the <fen>Dryee</fen>.
The sentient entity causes the Artifact to not function.
The device that no longer works.
An inanimate entity or force that renders the <fen>Artifact</fen> non-functional.
The time at which the event takes place.
The place at which the event takes place.
The <fen>Resource</fen> is a physical entity or an ability to perform work that was used in an earlier process, typically in pursuit of a goal.
The person or sentient entity that causes the death of the <fen>Victim</fen>.
The living entity that dies as a result of the killing.
An inanimate entity or process that causes the death of the <fen>Victim</fen>.
The method or action that the <fen>Killer</fen> or <fen>Cause</fen> performs resulting in the death of the <fen>Victim</fen>.
The device used by the <fen>Killer</fen> to bring about the death of the <fen>Victim</fen>.
The point or period of time within which the <fen>Victim</fen> is killed.
The location where the death took place.
listRoleExamples: <fex>The rockslide</fex> killed nearly half of the climbers.
The flood exterminated the rats <fex>by cutting off access to food</fex>.
It's difficult to suicide <fex>with only a pocketknife</fex>.
There is no evidence that the royal family was killed <fex>during the destruction</fex> at this site.
Apparently there were two murders <fex>in Atherton</fex> in one week.
